  "texts": [
    "A noteworthy observation was the apparent inverse relationship between readability and scoring on our checklist.",
    "While GPT-generated abstracts adeptly summarised studies and communicated their implications, they frequently lacked the specific details to score favourably on our checklist.",
    "Although direct measurement of readability was beyond the scope of this study, our findings were corroborated by Eppler et al.",
    "in which GPT-generated texts outperformed original abstracts in the Global Readability Score, Flesch Kincade Reading Ease and other various readability metrics [14].",
    "Therefore, AI could serve as an invaluable tool in translating complex scientific texts into more accessible versions, hence promoting higher level of comprehension and engagement from the general public."
  ],
